
[1]servitude

   SERV'ITUDE, n. [L. servitudo or servitus. See Serve.]

   1. The condition of a slave; the state of involuntary subjection to a
   master; slavery; bondage. Such is the state of slaves in America. A
   large portion of the human race is in servitude.

   2. The state of a servant. [Less common and less proper.]

   3. The condition of a conquered country.

   4. A state of slavish dependence. Some persons may be in love with
   splendid servitude.

   5. Servants, collectively. [Not in use.]
